-♪ FOREVER AND ALWAYS,
I'M ALWAYS HERE ♪

03:25.683 --> 03:26.641
-HELLO, MITCH.

03:26.771 --> 03:27.903
-MORNING.

03:28.686 --> 03:29.905
-OH, NO.

03:30.035 --> 03:30.906
-YEAH.

03:32.081 --> 03:33.561
IT'S NOT A LOCAL TAGGER, EITHER.

03:33.691 --> 03:34.866
IT'S SOMEBODY NEW.

03:34.997 --> 03:36.564
-OH, GREAT.

03:36.694 --> 03:38.392
NOW WE'LL BE STUCK IN
THE MIDDLE OF A TURF WAR.

03:39.828 --> 03:42.178
WE'LL BE PAINTING OVER
THIS WALL EVERY DAY.

03:43.658 --> 03:45.442
THIS ISN'T YOUR TURF,
DAMN-IT. IT'S MINE!

03:45.573 --> 03:46.835
-EASY, TAKE IT EASY.

03:46.965 --> 03:49.141
-I CAN'T HELP IT.
IT REALLY MAKES ME MAD.

03:49.272 --> 03:50.795
PEOPLE COME TO THE
BEACH TO ESCAPE

03:50.926 --> 03:52.319
FROM GANGS AND GRAFFITI.

03:52.449 --> 03:54.582
-PEOPLE ALSO COME TO
THE BEACH WITH PROBLEMS.

03:54.712 --> 03:56.540
-WELL, THAT DOESN'T MEAN
THEY CAN TAKE IT OUT ON US.

04:03.199 --> 04:04.679
-OKAY LET'S GIVE
A LITTLE POLISH,

04:04.809 --> 04:05.593
MAKE IT LOOK NICE.

04:05.723 --> 04:06.637
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

04:19.824 --> 04:22.043
NOW, LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
FOR MY NEXT TRICK,

04:22.174 --> 04:23.219
I'D LIKE TO...

04:24.612 --> 04:26.744
IT'S A... IT'S A VERY
DIFFICULT TRICK.

04:30.922 --> 04:32.663
-EXCUSE ME, ARE YOU
THE GREAT MARONI?

04:32.794 --> 04:35.013
-OH, MY REPUTATION PRECEDES ME.

04:35.144 --> 04:36.885
-YOU'RE NOT GOING TO LET
ALL THESE BLOW AWAY, ARE YOU?

04:37.015 --> 04:38.408
-OH, GOOD HEAVENS, NO.

04:38.539 --> 04:40.367
THIS IS MY ENTIRE
ADVERTISING CAMPAIGN.

04:40.497 --> 04:44.066
-WHAT IS THIS DEATH-DEFYING,
UNDERWATER ESCAPE ACT
YOU'RE GONNA DO?

04:44.196 --> 04:45.720
-OH WELL, IT'S REALLY
QUITE MAGNIFICENT.

04:45.850 --> 04:48.853
I'M COVERED IN
CHAINS AND SHACKLED,

04:48.984 --> 04:50.768
75-POUND BALL
ATTACHED TO MY FEET,

04:50.899 --> 04:52.683
AND I LEAP OFF THE
PIER INTO THE OCEAN.

04:53.641 --> 04:55.164
-WHY?
-WHY NOT?

04:55.295 --> 04:57.471
-WELL, FOR ONE THING,
IT'S ILLEGAL.

04:58.254 --> 04:59.734
AND FOR ANOTHER, IT'S CRAZY.

04:59.864 --> 05:01.083
-OH, NO, NO, NO.

05:01.213 --> 05:02.084
NO, IT'S MAGIC.

05:03.259 --> 05:04.521
DO YOU BELIEVE
IN MAGIC, MISS...

05:04.652 --> 05:06.741
-PARKER. CJ.

05:06.871 --> 05:09.178
-IT'S A PLEASURE
TO MEET YOU, CJ.

05:09.744 --> 05:11.572
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY SAY
ABOUT A BIRD IN THE HAND?

05:12.181 --> 05:13.617
IT'S WORTH TWO IN THE TOWER.

05:40.949 --> 05:41.950
-SOMETHING TELLS ME
THOSE ARE THE ONES

05:42.080 --> 05:43.212
WHO SHOULD BE DOING THIS.

05:47.608 --> 05:48.826
-COME ON, BACO. LET'S ROLL.

05:50.785 --> 05:51.829
-YOU'RE DRIPPING.

05:52.569 --> 05:53.918
-OH, YUCK!

05:56.747 --> 05:58.009
ON TOP OF ALL THIS,
I'M GOING TO SMELL LIKE

05:58.140 --> 05:59.228
TURPENTINE ALL DAY.

06:00.098 --> 06:01.317
I HATE THAT SMELL.

06:05.060 --> 06:06.104
-MITCH: HEY, CHECK THIS OUT!

06:06.931 --> 06:07.802
-STEPHANIE: WHAT?

06:09.151 --> 06:10.892
-WOW, THAT LOOKS LIKE CARLOS.

06:14.243 --> 06:15.375
-WHO'S CARLOS?

06:15.984 --> 06:17.159
-IT'S OUR NEW REPLACEMENT.

06:17.768 --> 06:19.509
HE'S FILLING IN WHILE
NEWMIE'S ON VACATION.

06:24.471 --> 06:26.777
-YOU MADE A PERSONNEL
DECISION WITHOUT CONSULTING ME?

06:26.908 --> 06:29.998
-OH, LIGHTEN UP.
YOU WEREN'T AROUND AT THE TIME.

06:30.128 --> 06:32.217
TRUST ME, YOU WON'T
BE DISAPPOINTED.

06:32.348 --> 06:34.089
-WHAT IS THAT SUPPOSED TO MEAN?

06:34.219 --> 06:36.918
-WELL, IT JUST MEANS THAT
I THINK MAYBE YOU AND CARLOS

06:37.048 --> 06:39.007
WILL, YOU KNOW, HIT IT OFF.

06:41.401 --> 06:44.099
-MITCH, I DON'T NEED YOU
TO FIX ME UP, THANK YOU.

06:44.926 --> 06:46.971
-STEPHANIE, WHEN WAS THE
LAST TIME YOU WERE ON A DATE?

06:48.016 --> 06:49.452
-I GO ON DATES ALL THE TIME.

06:50.845 --> 06:52.629
I MEAN, JUST BECAUSE I DON'T
DISCUSS MY LOVE LIFE WITH YOU

06:52.760 --> 06:53.935
DOESN'T MEAN I DON'T HAVE ONE.

06:54.065 --> 06:55.284
-OKAY, OKAY, FORGET IT.

06:55.415 --> 06:56.677
I'M SORRY I EVEN BROUGHT IT UP.

06:56.807 --> 06:58.635
-WELL, I HOPE
HE'S A DECENT LIFEGUARD.

06:58.766 --> 07:00.550
-MITCH: CARLOS HAS WON EVERY
SOUTH BAY COMPETITION

07:00.681 --> 07:01.638
IN THE LAST THREE YEARS.

07:01.769 --> 07:03.466
HE'S AN EXCELLENT LIFEGUARD.

07:04.032 --> 07:05.163
WE'RE LUCKY HE WAS AVAILABLE.

07:05.816 --> 07:06.643
-WHICH ONE IS HE?

07:07.165 --> 07:08.297
-THE ONE ON THE LEFT.

07:20.135 --> 07:23.834
-WELL, HE SURE KNOWS
HOW TO MAKE AN ENTRANCE.

07:27.185 --> 07:28.665
-HEY HEY!
-HEY, MITCH!

07:28.796 --> 07:29.840
GOOD TO SEE YOU, MAN.

07:29.971 --> 07:31.233
HOW'S IT GOING?

07:31.363 --> 07:32.843
-ONCE A HOTDOG,
ALWAYS A HOTDOG, HUH?

07:32.974 --> 07:33.888
-WHAT CAN I SAY?

07:34.018 --> 07:35.498
MY CAR BROKE DOWN.

07:35.629 --> 07:36.499
DIDN'T WANT TO BE LATE
FIRST DAY ON THE JOB.

07:37.587 --> 07:39.937
HI, I'M CARLOS BAERGA.
-HI.

07:40.068 --> 07:42.374
-OH, I'M SORRY. THIS IS
LIEUTENANT STEPHANIE HOLDEN.

07:42.505 --> 07:43.898
-NICE TO MEET YOU, LIEUTENANT.

07:44.594 --> 07:45.465
-STEPHANIE.

07:46.161 --> 07:47.379
WELCOME TO BAYWATCH.

07:48.555 --> 07:50.426
OH, I'M SORRY.

07:53.385 --> 07:54.474
-THAT'S OKAY.

07:57.955 --> 08:00.088
-SINCE YOU'RE PART-TIME,
I'LL GOT A WAIVER ON THE HAIR.

08:00.218 --> 08:01.655
JUST BE SURE YOU PUT
IT IN A PONYTAIL, ALL RIGHT?

08:01.785 --> 08:03.352
-NO PROBLEM.
-OKAY.

08:03.483 --> 08:04.701
-LISTEN, LET ME JUST
TAKE CARE OF MY GEAR,

08:04.832 --> 08:06.268
AND THEN I'M ALL YOURS, OKAY?

08:06.398 --> 08:07.791
-YOU GOT IT.

08:10.402 --> 08:13.231
WHY, LIEUTENANT, I
BELIEVE YOU'RE DROOLING.

08:15.582 --> 08:17.932
DO I TAKE CARE OF YOU OR WHAT?

08:20.500 --> 08:22.980
-[OVERLAPPING CHATTER]

08:27.419 --> 08:31.119
-[WOMEN GRUNTING]

08:32.424 --> 08:33.643
-THANKS, HOBIE!

08:33.774 --> 08:35.297
-NO PROBLEM.
-ALL RIGHT, THIS IS IT!

08:35.427 --> 08:36.645
-MATCH POINT.

08:43.957 --> 08:47.439
-[WOMEN GRUNTING]

08:51.139 --> 08:54.011
-ALL RIGHT, STEP RIGHT UP.
GET AN ICE COLD A&W.

08:54.142 --> 08:57.972
I GOT ROOT BEER, DIET ROOTBEER,
CREAM SODA, ANYTHING.

09:03.412 --> 09:04.413
-I'LL HAVE ONE.

09:05.066 --> 09:05.936
-ME TOO.

09:06.763 --> 09:07.590
-THANKS.

09:08.983 --> 09:09.853
-THANKS.

09:14.597 --> 09:16.904
-STEPHANIE:
SO, YOU AND MITCH
ARE OLD FRIENDS, HUH?

09:18.079 --> 09:20.385
-YEP, HE TRAINED
ME IN ROOKIE SCHOOL.

09:20.516 --> 09:21.604
-OH.

09:22.170 --> 09:23.650
-I'D ALWAYS HOPED TO GET
A CHANCE TO WORK WITH HIM.

09:24.433 --> 09:27.392
YOU KNOW, WATCH THE
MASTER IN ACTION.

09:27.523 --> 09:29.873
-[BOTH LAUGH]

09:30.874 --> 09:32.397
-I THINK YOU'RE GONNA
LIKE IT HERE AT BAYWATCH.

09:33.355 --> 09:34.443
-YEAH.

09:35.444 --> 09:37.620
-NOT THAT WE DON'T HAVE
OUR SHARE OF PROBLEMS.

09:42.582 --> 09:43.800
-SO I SEE.

09:44.584 --> 09:46.194
-HAVE YOU EVER HAD
TO DEAL WITH GANGS?

09:48.109 --> 09:49.414
-NOT AS A LIFEGUARD.

09:52.853 --> 09:55.769
-WELL, AS LIFEGUARDS
IT'S OUR JOB

09:55.899 --> 09:57.422
TO MAKE SURE THAT
THE BEACHES ARE SAFE.

09:58.815 --> 10:00.991
IF THE BEACHES AREN'T SAFE,
THEN PEOPLE STOP COMING.

10:02.166 --> 10:03.603
IF PEOPLE STOP COMING, THEN...

10:05.300 --> 10:07.084
WELL, WE'LL ALL BE OUT OF WORK.

10:08.042 --> 10:09.347
-CAN'T LET THAT HAPPEN.

10:09.870 --> 10:11.393
I'VE STILL GOT ANOTHER YEAR
OF LAW SCHOOL TO PAY FOR.

10:11.523 --> 10:12.873
-OH, YOU'RE GONNA
BE AN ATTORNEY?

10:13.700 --> 10:14.570
-YEP.

10:15.876 --> 10:19.096
JUST WHAT THE WORLD
NEEDS, ANOTHER LAWYER.

10:19.227 --> 10:20.402
-[BOTH LAUGH]

10:36.070 --> 10:37.767
-[SPEAKING SPANISH]

11:20.767 --> 11:21.681
-WHAT'S UP, MAN?

11:23.421 --> 11:25.772
YOU MAKE A LOT OF
MONEY TODAY, NO?

11:25.902 --> 11:27.208
HUH?

11:27.338 --> 11:28.600
-LET'S SEE IT, HOMES.

11:37.784 --> 11:39.350
-GIVE IT UP, MAN.

11:45.922 --> 11:46.793
THAT'S BETTER.

11:47.358 --> 11:48.577
-[GROUP SPEAKING SPANISH]

11:48.708 --> 11:49.796
-THAT'S RIGHT, BABY.

11:50.535 --> 11:52.407
-WHAT YOU GOT IN THERE?
-NOTHING.

11:52.537 --> 11:53.843
-LUIS, LET'S GO.

11:54.844 --> 11:57.194
-YEAH, VAMOS.
HEY, I'M THIRSTY, MAN.

12:02.809 --> 12:04.201
-UH-OH.

12:04.332 --> 12:05.507
STEPHANIE, IT LOOKS
LIKE TROUBLE OVER THERE.

12:10.425 --> 12:11.992
-OH MY GOD, THAT'S HOBIE!

12:12.819 --> 12:15.517
BARNETT, GET OVER THERE, QUICK!

12:16.736 --> 12:18.868
-[SIREN WAILING]

12:28.051 --> 12:29.139
-WOMAN: ADELSA!

12:31.968 --> 12:33.187
-STEPHANIE: HOBIE!

12:43.937 --> 12:44.894
-AW, MAN.

12:45.025 --> 12:46.635
-HOBIE, WHAT HAPPENED?

12:46.766 --> 12:48.245
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

12:48.376 --> 12:49.986
-YEAH, THEY JUMPED ME
AND TOOK ALL MY MONEY.

12:50.117 --> 12:51.771
-THEY DIDN'T HURT YOU, THOUGH?

12:53.163 --> 12:55.165
[CHEERING]

13:03.652 --> 13:04.958
-DID YOU GET A
LOOK AT ANY OF THEM?

13:05.088 --> 13:06.089
-NOT REALLY.

13:06.786 --> 13:08.439
-LISTEN, I KNOW THIS HIT
YOU GUYS WHERE YOU LIVE,

13:08.570 --> 13:10.702
BUT THIS IS A POLICE PROBLEM,
NOT A LIFEGUARD PROBLEM.

13:10.833 --> 13:13.096
THESE KIDS ARE ARMED, SO
LET US HANDLE IT, OKAY.

13:14.010 --> 13:15.055
-OKAY.

13:21.409 --> 13:22.453
-YOU OKAY?

13:23.803 --> 13:25.500
-NEVER HAD A BETTER DAY.

13:25.630 --> 13:26.806
-WHAT HAPPENED?

13:26.936 --> 13:28.372
-I GOT JUMPED BY
SOME GANG BANGERS.

13:28.503 --> 13:29.634
THEY TOOK ALL MY MONEY.

13:29.765 --> 13:31.636
I HAD NO CHOICE. THEY HAD A GUN.

13:31.767 --> 13:33.160
-YOU DID THE RIGHT THING, PAL.

13:33.290 --> 13:34.857
WHEN THAT HAPPENS, YOU
GIVE THEM WHAT THEY WANT.

13:36.032 --> 13:36.903
SORRY, THOUGH.

15:48.469 --> 15:50.079
-I SHOULD'VE KNOWN IT WAS YOU.

15:50.210 --> 15:52.081
WHAT DO YOU THINK YOU'RE DOING?
-REHEARSING.

15:52.212 --> 15:53.648
I HAVE TO HOLD MY
BREATH FOR THREE MINUTES

15:53.778 --> 15:55.345
WHILE COMPLETELY SUBMERGED.

15:55.476 --> 15:57.304
IT TAKES INCREDIBLE
SELF-DISCIPLINE.

15:58.044 --> 15:59.175
-I THOUGHT YOU WERE DEAD.

16:00.655 --> 16:02.918
-DO YOU KNOW HOUDINI COULD
STAY UNDERWATER FOR SIX MINUTES?

16:03.614 --> 16:04.528
-WELL, NOT ON MY BEACH.

16:05.268 --> 16:07.575
-LOOK, I'M SORRY
IF I ALARMED YOU.

16:08.315 --> 16:09.881
-LOOK, I'M A LITTLE
CONCERNED ABOUT

16:10.012 --> 16:11.361
THIS DEATH-DEFYING
STUNT YOU'RE GONNA PULL.

16:12.058 --> 16:13.059
-HOW'S THAT?

16:13.624 --> 16:15.104
-I HAVE TO MAKE SURE
IT'S GONNA BE SAFE.

16:16.018 --> 16:17.367
-WELL, I GIVE YOU MY
WORD AS A GENTLEMAN.

16:17.498 --> 16:19.282
-UNFORTUNATELY
THAT'S NOT ENOUGH.

16:19.413 --> 16:21.763
YOU'RE GONNA NEED A PERMIT
TO PULL OF THIS STUNT,

16:21.893 --> 16:23.983
AND I'M GONNA MAKE SURE
THAT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN

16:24.113 --> 16:26.637
UNLESS I'M CONVINCED YOU'RE
NOT GONNA KILL YOURSELF.

16:27.290 --> 16:28.596
-YOU CAN'T EXPECT
ME TO TELL YOU HOW

16:28.726 --> 16:29.727
I PERFORM THE ESCAPE.

16:30.337 --> 16:32.861
CJ, A MAGICIAN NEVER
REVEALS HIS SECRETS!

16:32.992 --> 16:34.689
-NEVER SAY NEVER, MARONI.

16:35.342 --> 16:36.604
NOW, TALK TO ME OR I'M GONNA

16:36.734 --> 16:38.084
PULL THE PLUG ON
YOUR PERFORMANCE.

16:38.998 --> 16:40.086
-OKAY.

16:40.695 --> 16:42.436
YOU'VE GOT TO PROMISE YOU'LL
NEVER REVEAL THE SECRET.

16:42.566 --> 16:43.480
-MY LIPS ARE SEALED.

16:44.394 --> 16:46.179
-WELL, YOU'VE HEARD OF
THE SLEIGHT OF HAND.

16:47.093 --> 16:49.530
WELL, THIS IS A
VARIATION ON THE THEME.

16:56.754 --> 16:57.668
-THAT'S IT?

16:58.365 --> 16:59.583
THAT'S THE SECRET?

17:00.497 --> 17:02.282
YOU HIDE A KEY
BETWEEN YOUR TOES?

17:02.412 --> 17:04.414
-WELL, NOW YOU SEE
WHY WE NEVER REVEAL

17:04.545 --> 17:05.589
HOW OUR TRICKS ARE DONE.

17:06.242 --> 17:07.635
IT RUINS THE ILLUSION.

17:36.229 --> 17:37.273
-HERE YOU GO!

17:37.404 --> 17:38.535
-THANKS.

17:45.020 --> 17:45.803
-HOLA, ADELSA.

17:45.934 --> 17:49.416
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

17:49.546 --> 17:50.417
-NO.

17:50.547 --> 17:53.507
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

17:53.637 --> 17:54.508
-NO!

17:54.638 --> 17:55.552
-I'M TAKING YOU HOME.

17:55.683 --> 17:56.684
-LIKE HELL YOU ARE.

17:58.990 --> 18:00.470
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

18:04.300 --> 18:05.388
[SPEAKS IN SPANISH]

18:05.997 --> 18:06.868
-BROTHER?

18:09.000 --> 18:10.654
SHE NEVER TOLD ME
ABOUT NO BROTHER.

18:13.788 --> 18:17.096
WHAT? YOU THINK I'M
AFRAID OF YOU, HUH?

18:17.922 --> 18:19.098
'CAUSE YOU'RE A LIFEGUARD?

18:21.143 --> 18:22.927
ADELSA IS MINE.

18:25.278 --> 18:26.409
YOU STAY AWAY FROM HER.

18:38.769 --> 18:39.727
-MORNING!

18:39.857 --> 18:40.902
-HI.

18:44.645 --> 18:45.646
HOW'S HOBIE?

18:46.995 --> 18:49.302
-NOT GOOD, HE'S
STILL PRETTY SHOOK UP.

18:49.911 --> 18:51.130
WOULDN'T LEAVE THE
HOUSE THIS MORNING.

18:52.131 --> 18:53.436
-YOU KNOW WHAT'S WEIRD, THOUGH?

18:55.134 --> 18:56.700
WHEN GARNER ASKED CARLOS IF HE'D

18:56.831 --> 18:58.485
GOTTEN A GOOD LOOK AT
ANY OF THOSE GANG BANGERS,

18:58.615 --> 18:59.529
CARLOS SAID NO.

19:00.182 --> 19:01.401
-WHY IS THAT WEIRD?

19:02.445 --> 19:04.360
-WELL, I SAW HIM LOOK
RIGHT AT ONE OF THOSE GIRLS.

19:05.013 --> 19:06.449
HE DEFINITELY SAW HER. I KNOW.

19:06.580 --> 19:07.581
[PHONE RINGING]

19:08.408 --> 19:09.713
-BUCHANNON.

19:09.844 --> 19:11.411
-YEAH, I THOUGHT
I ASKED YOU PEOPLE

19:11.541 --> 19:12.803
TO STAY ON THE SIDELINES.

19:12.934 --> 19:14.979
-WE ARE. WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

19:15.110 --> 19:17.547
-WELL, YOUR NEW GUY
IS ON THE PIER TAILING
A COUPLE OF GANG BANGERS.

19:17.678 --> 19:18.940
ANY IDEA WHAT THAT'S ALL ABOUT?

19:22.378 --> 19:23.814
MITCH: GARNER,
STEPHANIE'S ON HER WAY.

19:30.821 --> 19:35.522
-[ROCK SONG PLAYING]

19:36.392 --> 19:40.701
-♪ YOU CAN FEEL IT IN THE AIR
FEEL IT IN THE HEAT ♪

19:42.181 --> 19:45.706
♪ THERE'S SOMETHING GOING DOWN
AND HITTING THE STREET ♪

19:47.316 --> 19:51.712
♪ EVERYBODY'S ON THE EDGE
WAITING ON A SIGN ♪

19:52.887 --> 19:56.717
♪ AND THE PEOPLE ON THE SIDEWALK
MOVE OUTTA LINE ♪

19:57.892 --> 20:02.984
-♪ WE GOT BOOTS ON THE GROUND
AND WE WON'T BACK DOWN ♪

20:03.114 --> 20:05.552
♪ GONNA BE A STANDOFF

20:08.816 --> 20:13.864
♪ YOU CAN FEEL IT ON THE STREET
THERE'S NO TAKIN' DEFEAT ♪

20:13.995 --> 20:16.215
♪ GONNA BE A STANDOFF

21:04.045 --> 21:08.005
♪ THE HIGHER THE HURDLE
THE HARDER WE FIGHT ♪

21:09.572 --> 21:13.663
♪ THOUGH WE TRY TO FIND A REASON
IT AIN'T BLACK OR WHITE ♪

21:14.882 --> 21:18.799
♪ BUT WE CAN'T LET OUR REPUTATION
