35:59.505 --> 36:01.507
AND BRAD, WORK THE
SOUTH BAY BEACH TODAY.

36:01.637 --> 36:03.204
-LUIS MADE BAIL THIS MORNING.

36:03.335 --> 36:05.424
HE'S BACK ON THE STREET
AND PROBABLY THE BEACH.

36:05.554 --> 36:07.034
HAVE YOUR PEOPLE
KEEP THEIR EYES OPEN,

36:07.165 --> 36:09.079
AND IF ANYONE SEES
ANYTHING GOING DOWN,

36:09.210 --> 36:10.777
PICK UP A PHONE AND CALL.

36:10.907 --> 36:12.344
WE'LL TAKE CARE OF IT.

36:58.346 --> 37:00.000
-HEY, GET BACK HERE!

37:06.833 --> 37:08.095
-STEPHANIE BACK YET?

37:08.704 --> 37:10.010
-WHAT'D HE LOOK LIKE?

37:11.272 --> 37:13.100
ALL RIGHT, LET ME GET WORD
OUT AND I'LL CALL YOU BACK.

37:13.231 --> 37:14.406
ALL RIGHT.

37:14.536 --> 37:15.798
-THAT WAS BARNETT.

37:15.929 --> 37:17.626
SOMEBODY JUST RIPPED
OFF HIS TRUCK.

37:19.802 --> 37:20.847
-WHAT'S GOING ON?

37:21.717 --> 37:23.502
-SOMEBODY STOLE
BARNETT'S TRUCK.

37:27.854 --> 37:30.770
[PHONE RINGING]

37:42.477 --> 37:43.391
-TOWER 18.

37:43.522 --> 37:45.263
-CARLOS, I JUST
TALKED TO GARNER.

37:45.393 --> 37:46.612
HE SAID THAT LUIS HAS
BEEN RELEASED ON BAIL.

37:46.742 --> 37:48.875
-STEPHANIE, I TOLD YA,
NOTHING'S GONNA HAPPEN.

37:49.005 --> 37:50.485
-I KNOW WHAT YOU
TOLD ME, JUST LISTEN.

37:50.616 --> 37:52.182
ONE OF OUR LIFEGUARD
TRUCKS HAS BEEN STOLEN.

37:52.313 --> 37:54.402
NOW, IT COULD BE THAT ONE
THING HAS NOTHING TO DO

37:54.533 --> 37:56.056
WITH THE OTHER, BUT
I JUST DON'T THINK
WE SHOULD TAKE ANY CHANCES.

37:57.100 --> 37:58.188
CARLOS?

37:59.494 --> 38:00.843
CARLOS, ARE YOU THERE?

38:18.774 --> 38:19.993
-COME ON!

38:31.265 --> 38:32.919
[GROANS]

38:40.056 --> 38:41.841
-ARGH!

38:42.711 --> 38:46.149
[SIREN]

38:58.727 --> 39:00.338
-ALL RIGHT, PAL. LET'S GO.

39:03.776 --> 39:05.865
-CARLOS, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

39:06.518 --> 39:07.736
-YEAH.

39:08.476 --> 39:10.304
JUST DON'T ASK ME TO DANCE.

39:14.090 --> 39:15.657
-STEPHANIE, GET REAL.

39:15.788 --> 39:17.572
THERE'S NO WAY THORPE'S
GONNA APPROVE THIS TRANSFER.

39:17.703 --> 39:18.791
-WHY NOT?

39:18.921 --> 39:20.183
-WHY NOT? WHERE
ARE WE GONNA GET

39:20.314 --> 39:22.577
THE FUNDING FOR
ADDITIONAL PERSONNEL?

39:22.708 --> 39:25.145
DIDN'T YOU GET HIS LAST
MEMO ON BUDGET CUTBACKS?

39:25.275 --> 39:26.973
-WELL, I THOUGHT YOU SAID
CHIEF THORPE OWED YOU A FAVOR.

39:27.103 --> 39:28.540
-HE DOES.

39:28.670 --> 39:29.889
AND I'M SAVING IT FOR
SOMETHING IMPORTANT.

39:30.019 --> 39:30.890
-OH, MITCH.

39:31.020 --> 39:32.413
THIS IS IMPORTANT.

39:32.544 --> 39:33.936
-COME ON, YOU'RE TELLING
ME YOU REALLY WANT

39:34.067 --> 39:36.504
CARLOS TO WORK HERE
ON A PERMANENT BASIS?

39:36.635 --> 39:38.506
REALLY? I MEAN,
WON'T IT BE TOO MUCH

39:38.637 --> 39:40.203
OF A DISTRACTION FOR YOU?

39:40.334 --> 39:41.901
I MEAN, ARE YOU SURE YOU'LL
BE ABLE TO CONCENTRATE?

39:42.031 --> 39:43.206
-VERY FUNNY.

39:43.337 --> 39:44.599
[LAUGHTER]

39:45.992 --> 39:47.341
-HI, GUYS.
-MITCH: HEY.

39:47.472 --> 39:49.430
-HI.
-CARLOS: HI.

39:49.561 --> 39:51.301
-WHAT HAPPENED? I THOUGHT
IT WAS JUST A SPRAIN.

39:51.432 --> 39:52.390
-YEAH, ME TOO.

39:52.520 --> 39:54.174
BUT THE SWELLING NEVER WENT DOWN

39:54.304 --> 39:55.480
SO I HAD AN MRI.

39:56.306 --> 39:58.526
TURNS OUT I TORE THE
ANTERIOR CRUCIATE LIGAMENT.

39:59.266 --> 40:00.310
